  <front>
   <head>Metrical Feet: Lesson for a Boy</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="+-+-+-+">Trochee trips from long to short.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+-+">From long to long in solemn sort.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="3" met="++-+++-+--">Slow Spondee stalks; strong foot! yet ill able</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="4" met="+--+--+--+--">Ever to come up with Dactyl trisyllable.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="5" met="-+-+-+-+">Iambics march from short to long.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="6" met="--+--+--+--+">With a leap and a bound the swift Anapests throng.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
